<title>USA: Microsoft to offer First Call on desktop.</title>
<headline>Microsoft to offer First Call on desktop.</headline>
<dateline>BOSTON 1997-07-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Call Corp said Monday it has agreed to develop content with Microsoft Corp for an active channel on Microsoft's Internet Explorer 4.0 software.</p>
<p>The First Call channel will use so-called &quot;push&quot; technologies to offer research notes, ratings and recommendations from major Wall Street firms' desktop computers.</p>
<p>Consensus earnings and recommendation data will be available only to individual investors.</p>
<p>First Call, part of Thomson Corp's Thomson Financial Services, said the First Call Notes product currently is viewed at over 9,000 desktops in the United States.</p>
